      "latency_seconds": 6.377,
      "answer": "[2] [3]\n\nThe evidence indicates that the approval for whether new article attributes are useful rather than unmanaged data requires validation and is currently an open question. Specifically, it states that \"Who owns article attributes by type?\" is a topic that needs validation due to the risk of attributes becoming unmanaged without clear ownership across support, assets, finance or other teams [2]. This implies that there is no current decision on who should approve this, but it requires validation and clear ownership to prevent data from becoming unmanaged."
